experience archaeological sensibility and archaeological imagination are terms to summarize components of these mediating and transformative practices sensibility refers us to the perceptual components of how we engage with the remains of the past imagination refers us to the creative component to the transforming work that is done on what is left over forthcoming archaeopaedia a glossary of the archaeological imagination http archaeopaedia com cover images edit this page attach file add image references print page last modified fri mar 02 2012 12 01 you must signin to post comments group admin versions track changes site home michael shanks the archaeological imagination
